# Project Architecture & General Rules

- Stack: Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + Zod + React Hook Form + Zustand.
- Top-level layers:
  - `src/app`: framework shell, layouts, route entrypoints.
  - `src/features`: feature modules (ui, hooks, state, actions).
  - `src/shared`: reusable components, constants, hooks, types, utilities.
- Dependency direction: `shared` -> `features` -> `app`.
- Never import `features` from `shared`.
- Keep route files in `src/app` thin; push domain logic to `src/features`.

## TypeScript & Style

- Avoid `any`; use explicit types for public APIs.
- Prefer named exports over default exports.
- Keep files focused; avoid unrelated helpers in the same file.
- Destructure object params in function signatures.
- Prefer object parameters over positional arguments for complex inputs.

## State, Validation, and Forms

- Use feature-scoped Zustand stores where client state is needed.
- Keep Zod schemas close to the feature domain.
- Use React Hook Form with Zod resolvers for form validation.

## Next.js Rules

- Prefer Server Components by default; add `'use client'` only when required.
- Keep shared UI primitives in `src/shared/components`.
- Do not place business logic directly in `src/app/layout.tsx` or `src/app/page.tsx`.

## Package manager

- Use Bun as a primary package manager
- Manage features (disable/enable) using Bun if needed
